quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  17,50,"Say: if you become stone or iron"
  17,51,"or a creation which is great in your mind (you still will be resurrected). Then they are going to say: who returns us (to life)? Say: He who created you the first time. Then they are going to shake their heads at you and say: when is that? Say: perhaps it is close"
  17,52,"a day that He calls you, and you answer with His praise, and you think that you only stayed (dead) for a little while"
  17,53,And tell My servants to say that which is the best (and in the best manner). Indeed Satan brings about animosity between them. Indeed Satan is an obvious enemy for the human being
  17,54,Your Master knows you better. If He wants He has mercy on you or if He wants He punishes you. We did not send you as their advocate
  17,55,"And your Master knows better everyone in the skies and on the earth. And We have certainly preferred some prophets over the others, and We gave David the Psalms (Zabur)"
  17,56,"Say: call on those whom you claimed other than Him, they do not have any power to get rid of the trouble from you or change it"
  17,57,"Those whom they call on, they look for the mean to their Master, anyone of them who are closer (to God) and they hope for His mercy and they fear His punishment. Indeed your Master's punishment is to be avoided"
  17,58,There is not any town that We do not destroy it or punish it with a severe punishment before the resurrection day. That is written down in the book